**Risks:**
- Forward replay + registry resolution only stays simple while the gate passes
  round 1; a rerun would emit `review.r2` stages that default forward-replay
  resolution cannot name. Mitigation: gate is designed to pass round 1 (verified).
  If a future change makes it rerun, the example/test would need a `--runner`
  override on replay — note in README.
- Absolute script paths in the generated registry/workflow are intentional
  (runner cwd is the scratch worktree). Keep generation in walkthrough.sh / the
  test; do not commit a static registry with hardcoded paths.
- Low overall: reproduced end-to-end against the current binary with no engine edit.

